  "datePublished": "2026-03-05",
  "description": "A subgroup is a group that lives inside a larger group — a subset that is itself a group under the same operation. The even integers form a subgroup of the integers under addition: they are closed under addition (even plus even is even), they contain the identity element 0, and every even integer has an additive inverse that is also even. The odd integers do not form a subgroup: odd plus odd is even, so they are not closed under addition.\n",
